				h1.ar-heading.kx-bg.f-oku.wtxt who is KNOX?
				p.ar-text Behold The Boy Warlord KNOX! Despite his pompous speeches and aversion to combat, this teenaged crime boss is at the top of every government agency's most wanted list for murder, extortion, fraud and more. Wearing a mech suit stolen from a fallen superhero's grave, Knox concocts grand plans inside his remote mansion surrounded with hired criminals and feral dogs. Although KNOX's schemes never go as planned, his Villain Underground superteam has developed a dangerous reputation. When playing KNOX, give in to your greed. Draw as many cards as you can. Kill off your lackeys. Look out for number one.

				p.ar-text KNOX is an aggressive rushdown character who tramples over slow control and combo players. KNOX's MINION skill allows him to avoid big chunks of player damage without being forced to commit to armor or healing. As this skill is limited to Utilities, many of your aggressive cards can also be cashed-in to avoid damage. KNOX also loves to draw as many cards as possible in order to find aggressive threats and speed up the game.
	
				p.ar-text Playing KNOX means being comfortable with burning through your deck at a rapid pace and keeping the pressure up at any costs. This all-out play style means that the design team has classified Knox as an INTERMEDIATE character. Newer players may not immediately be comfortable with this approach due to Knox's fragility, but experienced KNOX players can be the scariest opponents to see across the table. If you want to be aggressive and back defensive players into a corner, consider hiring the boy warlord and his Villain Underground!
